<font color="#FF0000">NO TIME FOR GUILT</font><br>
<tt>Sat May 31  1:38:30 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Don't feel guilty for not being there with us in Vietnam.  Remember an often used quote 'freedom is not free'.  There is still much to do to make sure our freedom remains safe.  Remain an informed, active citizen involved in voting and influencing elected officials to support and uphold the tenets on which America was founded.  Your response to this task is more important now than responding to the 'call to arms' was then.  Respond to this call and you have no reason for guilt.
<p><code>-- merkleg@texas.net  (Gil Merkle) </code><p>


